TABBOULEH 2 x 425g tins lentils, drained and rinsed 3 spring onions, finely sliced handful fresh flat-leaf parsley, roughly chopped small handful fresh mint leaves, roughly chopped handful fresh coriander leaves, roughly chopped juice of 1 lemon 30ml (2 tbsp) good-quality olive oil salt and freshly ground black pepper, to taste TO SERVE baby exotic tomatoes, some sliced and others left whole fresh micro basil leaves, to garnish HOW TO DO IT 1. For the tabbouleh, combine all of the ingredients in a medium bowl. Taste and season well. Serve in bowls, topped with baby exotic tomatoes and micro basil leaves.